Access & Ability.title: Ceramics for All: Ages 15+
Access & Ability.description:
In this 6-week class, you will get to explore
handbuilding in ceramics. Try techniques like slab
construction, coil building, and sculpting. This
class (like all of our classes!) is inclusive of all; but artists who come with mentors, advocates, or aides and want to socialize with peers may use this class as a meet-up!

Access & Ability.title: GATORS Program; age 5-18
Access & Ability.description:
GATORS is an adaptive gym program designed for individuals of all abilities. It focuses on games, activities, tag, obstacles, relays, and sensory stimulation. It provides a calm environment where individuals can be physically active with minimal noise and distractions.

*For Spring Session 1, we will run normally week 1-5. Week 6 class, 04/05, is canceled and we will hold a make up on 04/12.*

Fee: This program is free to individuals enrolled in the Access and Ability Family Community Inclusion Grant. If your child is enrolled please reach out and we can help with registration so you do not have to pay the fee.

Fee: There is a $35.00 fee for individuals that are not enrolled in the Access and Ability Grant. There is a $60.00 program fee for non-ymca members.
Access & Ability.location: Hal Welsh East Area Family YMCA

Access & Ability.title: Y Social Circle: Sports of All Sorts
Access & Ability.description:
Join the Y Social Circle this Spring Season l! An opportunity to get together, stay healthy, happy and creative! All are welcome!

Sports of all Sorts is an opportunity to learn and play various recreational sports while having fun with your peers! We try different sports ranging from Golf to Yard Games.

Participants can be accompanied by a mentor or receive assistance from Access and Ability staff if needed. Please contact the Access and Ability Department with any questions.
Access & Ability.location: Hal Welsh East Area Family YMCA

Access & Ability.title: YPals Program; Ages 10-20
Access & Ability.description:
Ypals is a program designed for teens and young adults with all abilities to create meaningful relationships with peers. The program focuses on enhancing socialization skills through the use of games and activities.

Fee: This program is free to individuals enrolled in the Access and Ability Family Community Inclusion Grant. If your child is enrolled please reach out and we will help with the registration process so you do not have to pay the program fee.

Creative Writing.description: Have you been writing for children and wish you could share your work with other writers? Are you looking for a critique group? Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Fiction Reboot (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Share creative, insightful ideas for ongoing projects in a supportive environment and write new work. We will discuss techniques, our individual processes, and get some suggestions for outside reading.

Creative Writing.title: Finding Your Space (Hybrid)
Creative Writing.description: How can LGBTQ+ writers find space for our work and identify the literary traditions and present moments to which we may belong? Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Flash Nonfiction (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Flash Nonfiction is back! A generative workshop and critique for flash nonfiction writers -- essays of no more than 800 words. A welcome place for poets to try their hand at nonfiction and for non-fiction writers to tighten their work.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: I'm Talking Here: Diction in Playwriting (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Plays are built on engaging dialogue. We will explore ways to create vibrant characters through how they speak. A goal for this class is to complete a ten-minute play or scene in a longer work. This class is reserved for writers who have previously taken a playwriting class through the Writers Voice.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Introduction to Grantwriting (Online)
Creative Writing.description: This course provides an overview of how grants are made, finding opportunities and funders, and writing grants. Writers will develop a grant template for current or future opportunities. This course is for both individuals or organizations.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Introduction to Memoir (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Do you want to write a memoir or help a loved one write theirs? Using the StoryCorps interview questions and Modern Love?s ?36 Questions that Lead to Love,? as inspiration, this class helps you write a manuscript that is a soul-searching, intimate and satisfying. (Note: this is a 6-week class.)
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Mining the Body of Poetry (DWC)
Creative Writing.description: Get under the skin of your writing to learn how form supports content and how language stirs the mind and body by appealing to our senses. We?ll read and discuss poems to inspire and guide our writing.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Muse Writing (Online)
Creative Writing.description: This course helps poetry writers get past their conventional imagination by using free-writing and associative techniques when drafting poems. Readings of wild poems along with writing exercises will help students access their muses.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Poetry as Legacy (Online)
Creative Writing.description: How do you want to be remembered? What poems do you want to leave as your legacy? This is a safe place for exploring your most tender stories for those who mean the most to you.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Ready! Set! Go! (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Let the spring season fuel your creative spark. This course provides prompts and exercises to spur memory, imagination, and new poems. We?ll write, talk about our ?burning questions? and breakthroughs regarding the writing process, and share our work in this generative class.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Spring Reading Series Book Club (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Read and discuss the latest book by authors in our Visiting Author Reading Series. It?s a great way to prepare for our Friday night readings! Best of all, Book Club itself is free! You just purchase the books through the Writers Voice at a discount. Please register early to get your books on time.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Strategies in Revision (Online)
Creative Writing.description: This class introduces students to different ways of approaching revision, including strategies for structural and line-level editing, responding to feedback, and using revision to refine and expand our work.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: The Spring Flow (Thursdays) (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Our popular nonfiction critique workshop continues with weekly comments and critique. New members are welcome, so if you?re working on a project or need encouragement, join us!
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: The Spring Flow (Wednesday) (Online)
Creative Writing.description: Our popular nonfiction critique workshop continues with weekly comments and critique. New members are welcome, so if you?re working on a project or need encouragement, join us!
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: The Writer's Life, Part Three: Entering the Workshop (Online)
Creative Writing.description: The final class in the "Writer?s Life" series, ?Entering the Workshop,? is your chance to receive constructive feedback. Through the guidance of the instructor, you will receive focused peer critique that?s necessary to take your work to new heights!
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Writing About Historical Figures (Online)
Creative Writing.description: We?ll practice different ways to make historical figures accessible and alive in our poetry. Writers can write about various figures or focus on a single person. All are welcome!
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Writing Longer Work (DWC)
Creative Writing.description: Do you have a great idea for a book, but get stuck on the beginning? Do you write short stories, but want to make the leap to something longer? Through exercises and critiques, we will sharpen our skills for going the distance.  You don?t need to have started your book to take this class?just bring your ideas and your commitment!
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA

Creative Writing.title: Young Authors Academy 25SPR (Hybrid)
Creative Writing.description: If you are in grades 6 through 12, and are interested in creative writing, the Young Authors Academy is the place for you. The YAA is the Downtown Writers Center's teen writing program, and as a member, you'll work with the same terrific writers who teach in the regular DWC workshops. We'll help you polish the fundamentals of writing poems and stories, and drive you to push your writing to the next level.
Creative Writing.location: Downtown Writers Center at Downtown Syracuse YMCA
